inoceros phase” or examining the problem of tactility in Thomas Pynchon’s The Crying of Lot 49, Schmidgen reconfigures understandings of the dynamic phenomena of touch in media.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 0aHorns. 0aMass mediaxPhilosophy. 0aTouchxPhilosophy. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Media Studies.2bisacsh1 aSchott, Nils F.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDuke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311076691240uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781478022343zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781478022343423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781478022343/original  a978-3-11-076691-2  Duke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  aEBA_DUK_ALL  aEBA_DUK_EALL  aEBA_DUK_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles